=======================================================================

%^RED%^%^BOLD%^ SYNTAX :: %^RESET%^ set_taste ( target, message )
%^RED%^%^BOLD%^ SYNTAX :: %^RESET%^ set_taste ( target, function )

This function is present in all objects. It will add the taste named
in the string target into the object. Either a string message can be
defined or a function pointer (: :) .

see also ::

set_tastes, remove_taste, remove_tastes, query_taste, query_tastes

